title: Three injured in shooting in Rotterdam, police say
description: Three people have been injured in a shooting at a summer carnival in the Dutch city of Rotterdam.

title: Ukrainians travel to Liverpool for Pride march
description: Hundreds of LGBT+ Ukrainians took to the streets of Liverpool as the city hosted Pride on behalf of their country's capital, Kyiv.

title: Saudi football league has 'changed the market' and is here 'to stay', says Pep Guardiola
description: The Saudi Arabian football league has "changed the market" and is here "to stay", Manchester City manager Pep Guardiola has said.

title: 'A love letter to Sinead': Nothing Compares documentary will still air despite singer's death
description: Nothing Compares, a documentary about Sinead O'Connor, will still air on Saturday to provide viewers the opportunity to "hear her tell her side of the story", according to the filmmaker.

title: At least 10 killed and and many more injured in fireworks warehouse blast
description: A massive explosion at a fireworks warehouse in southern Thailand has killed at least 10 people and left more than 100 injured.

title: Italian PM hits out at 'false propaganda' around her right-wing government
description: Italian Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni has hailed her visit to Washington after what she said was "false propaganda" around her right-wing government.

title: England's Keira Walsh to sit out China match following knee injury
description: Keira Walsh has been ruled out of Tuesday's final Group D match against China PR following a knee injury.

title: Ukraine fencer assured of Olympic spot after penalty for handshake snub
description: A Ukrainian fencer has been assured by the Olympic authorities she can compete at next year's Paris games after she was disqualified from a key ranking event for refusing to shake hands with a Russian she had beaten.

title: Sweden lead Italy 4-0 in Group G: Women's World Cup latest
Trump joins Republican presidential candidate rivals at campaign dinner
description: Donald Trump has told supporters at an influential campaign event in Iowa he is the only Republican candidate who can beat President Joe Biden.

title: Four crew missing after Australian army helicopter crashes
description: A search is under way for four crew members of an Australian army helicopter after it crashed into the water off the Queensland coast.

title: Majority of fires in Greece were started by 'human hand', official says
description: The majority of the fires which have ravaged Greece in recent weeks were started by "human hand", one of the country's top climate officials has said.

title: Chinese families 'destroyed' by burden of facing rare disease ALS
description: In a small flat on China's east coast, a young woman is fighting a battle she cannot win.
